# Meshack Offei-Essah — Operational Efficiency Analysis

## Executive Summary
Optimisation framework built on practical event logistics experience and financial modelling, forecasting operational efficiency gains over a 3-year horizon.

## Key Insights
- Analysed high-pressure operational environments (concerts/sports venues)
- Identified **15–25% potential efficiency gains** via better forecasting and resource allocation
- Built scenario models showing clear cost-saving pathways without compromising service delivery
- Projected **£127k+ cumulative efficiency gain by Year 3** from a £500k revenue base

## Model Structure
3-tab Excel model with cross-sheet formula architecture:
- **Assumptions** — editable inputs (growth rate, cost targets, volume, pricing)
- **3-Year Forecast** — dynamic revenue, cost, efficiency gain, and margin calculations
- **Summary** — key insights and operational recommendations

## Recommendation
Adopt integrated spreadsheet-based forecasting tools for operational teams. Cost discipline at scale has a compounding effect — a 20% cost reduction in Year 1 generates £24k savings, growing to £127k by Year 3 as volume increases.

